  "prayerNafalBenefitLabel": "Benefit",
  "prayerNafalHadithReferencesLabel": "Hadith references",
  "prayerNafalNoteTitle": "Gentle fiqh note",
  "prayerNafalNoteBody": "These are friendly reminders for common nafal windows. Details and rakah counts may vary by madhhab and teacher, so follow trusted local guidance for rulings.",
  "prayerNafalTahajjudTitle": "Tahajjud",
  "prayerNafalTahajjudBadge": "Deep night",
  "prayerNafalTahajjudTime": "Last third of the night before Fajr",
  "prayerNafalTahajjudRakah": "2+",
  "prayerNafalTahajjudBenefit": "Turns the quiet night into du'a, repentance, and deeper focus.",
  "prayerNafalTahajjudBody": "Wake gently, pray in pairs, and keep the recitation calm. Even two focused raka'ahs can become the quietest anchor of the day.",
  "prayerNafalTahajjudHadith1Source": "Sahih Muslim 1163a",
  "prayerNafalTahajjudHadith1Body": "The best prayer after the obligatory prayer is night prayer.",
  "prayerNafalIshraqTitle": "Ishraq",
  "prayerNafalIshraqBadge": "After sunrise",
  "prayerNafalIshraqTime": "After sunrise has clearly passed",
  "prayerNafalIshraqRakah": "2",
  "prayerNafalIshraqBenefit": "Connects Fajr, dhikr, and a hopeful start to the morning.",
  "prayerNafalIshraqBody": "Wait until the forbidden sunrise window clears, then begin with a light heart and a short, sincere prayer.",
  "prayerNafalIshraqHadith1Source": "Jami' at-Tirmidhi 586",
  "prayerNafalIshraqHadith1Body": "Fajr in congregation, dhikr until sunrise, then two raka'ahs is reported with Hajj and Umrah reward.",
  "prayerNafalDuhaTitle": "Duha / Chasht",
  "prayerNafalDuhaBadge": "Bright morning",
  "prayerNafalDuhaTime": "Mid-morning until before Dhuhr",
  "prayerNafalDuhaRakah": "2-8",
  "prayerNafalDuhaBenefit": "Refreshes gratitude and covers the morning charity due from the body.",
  "prayerNafalDuhaBody": "Use the morning stretch for gratitude, provision, and renewed energy before the day gets heavy.",
  "prayerNafalDuhaHadith1Source": "Sahih Muslim 720",
  "prayerNafalDuhaHadith1Body": "Two raka'ahs of Duha suffice for the morning charity due from every joint.",
  "prayerNafalDuhaHadith2Source": "Sahih al-Bukhari 1178; Sahih Muslim 721a",
  "prayerNafalDuhaHadith2Body": "Abu Hurayrah was advised to keep Duha among regular acts.",
  "prayerNafalAwwabinTitle": "Awwabin",
  "prayerNafalAwwabinBadge": "Evening return",
  "prayerNafalAwwabinTime": "After Maghrib sunnah, before Isha",
  "prayerNafalAwwabinRakah": "2-6",
  "prayerNafalAwwabinBenefit": "Keeps the Maghrib-Isha window alive with short extra raka'ahs and dhikr.",
  "prayerNafalAwwabinBody": "Let the evening soften: return to Allah with short raka'ahs, dhikr, and a quieter transition toward Isha.",
  "prayerNafalAwwabinHadith1Source": "Jami' at-Tirmidhi 435; Sunan Ibn Majah 1167",
  "prayerNafalAwwabinHadith1Body": "Six raka'ahs after Maghrib are reported; scholars discuss the report's strength.",
  "prayerNafalAwwabinHadith2Source": "Sahih Muslim 748b",
  "prayerNafalAwwabinHadith2Body": "The name Salat al-Awwabin is also authentically used for the Duha-time prayer.",
  "prayerHowIntentionTitle": "Intention & readiness",
  "prayerHowIntentionBody": "Make wudu, face the qibla, and settle your intention in the heart before you begin.",
  "prayerHowQiyamTitle": "Qiyam",
  "prayerHowQiyamBody": "Stand calmly, say the opening takbir, recite Al-Fatihah, then recite what is easy from the Quran.",
  "prayerHowRukuTitle": "Ruku",
  "prayerHowRukuBody": "Bow with the back settled, glorify Allah, then rise with calm before going down.",
  "prayerHowSujoodTitle": "Sujood",
  "prayerHowSujoodBody": "Prostrate with humility, pause without rushing, then sit briefly and complete the second prostration.",
  "prayerHowTashahhudTitle": "Tashahhud",
  "prayerHowTashahhudBody": "In the final sitting, recite tashahhud and send salawat upon the Prophet, peace be upon him.",
  "prayerHowSalamTitle": "Salam",
  "prayerHowSalamBody": "End the prayer with salam, then remain present for short dhikr and du'a.",
  "prayerFocusFajrTitle": "Fajr Window",
  "prayerFocusFajrSubtitle": "Begin the day before the world gets loud.",
  "prayerFocusSunriseTitle": "Sunrise Pause",
  "prayerFocusSunriseSubtitle": "A quiet transition after Fajr; wait before optional Duha.",
  "prayerFocusDhuhrTitle": "Dhuhr Reset",
  "prayerFocusDhuhrSubtitle": "Let the middle of the day become a clean spiritual reset.",
  "prayerFocusAsrTitle": "Asr Guard",
  "prayerFocusAsrSubtitle": "Protect the late afternoon before tasks scatter your attention.",
  "prayerFocusMaghribTitle": "Maghrib Return",
  "prayerFocusMaghribSubtitle": "Move quickly from sunset into remembrance and gratitude.",
  "prayerFocusIshaTitle": "Isha Closure",
  "prayerFocusIshaSubtitle": "Close the day with calm, repentance, and preparation for Fajr.",
  "prayerNowFajrTitle": "Protect the dawn",
  "prayerNowFajrBody": "Before sunrise, protect the Fajr window. If you have not prayed, make wudu and pray now; if you have, stay with morning adhkar or Quran.",
  "prayerNowSunriseTitle": "Pause and remember",
  "prayerNowSunriseBody": "At exact sunrise avoid starting voluntary prayer; keep morning dhikr and wait until the sun has risen before Duha.",
  "prayerNowDhuhrTitle": "Reset the middle of the day",
  "prayerNowDhuhrBody": "Step away from work, renew wudu, and give the fard prayer an unhurried pocket of attention.",
  "prayerNowAsrTitle": "Guard the late afternoon",
  "prayerNowAsrBody": "Make Asr visible before the day becomes crowded. Pray with steady pace and leave a short moment for dhikr afterward.",
  "prayerNowMaghribTitle": "Move promptly",
  "prayerNowMaghribBody": "When Maghrib enters, shift quickly from sunset routines into salah, then return to family, food, or travel with a lighter heart.",
  "prayerNowIshaTitle": "Close the day cleanly",
  "prayerNowIshaBody": "Pray Isha before sleepiness takes over. Pair it with repentance, gratitude, and a simple plan for waking for Fajr.",
  "prayerSuggestionsFajrRaw": "Pray the two raka'at Sunnah before the fard when you are able.||Keep the recitation calm and bright, even if it is short.||After salah, spend a few minutes with morning adhkar or a small Quran portion.",
  "prayerSuggestionsSunriseRaw": "Continue morning adhkar while the sun rises.||Wait until the disliked sunrise moment passes before optional Duha.||Use the quiet transition to plan the next prayer instead of drifting.",
  "prayerSuggestionsDhuhrRaw": "Use the adhan as a hard pause from work or study.||Choose a quiet place before the day becomes crowded again.||Pair the prayer with a small gratitude check before returning to tasks.",
  "prayerSuggestionsAsrRaw": "Plan Asr before the late-afternoon rush begins.||Keep the pace steady rather than compressed.||Use one minute after salam to ask Allah for protection and consistency.",
  "prayerSuggestionsMaghribRaw": "Pray soon after adhan because the window feels short in daily life.||Keep food, family, and commute transitions from swallowing the prayer.||Follow with evening adhkar when your routine allows.",
  "prayerSuggestionsIshaRaw": "Pray before sleepiness makes focus heavy.||Prepare for Witr according to your practice after Isha.||Set up tomorrow's Fajr before bed: alarm, wudu plan, and sleep intention.",
  "prayerBestPracticesFajrRaw": "Sleep with Fajr in mind, not as an afterthought.||Avoid rushing the first prayer of the day; let it set the tone.||Use the stillness after Fajr for Quran, adhkar, or one sincere du'a.",
  "prayerBestPracticesSunriseRaw": "Do not treat sunrise as an obligatory prayer; it is a transition marker.||Stay away from voluntary prayer at the exact sunrise moment.||Return to optional worship after the sun has risen and the time is clear.",
  "prayerBestPracticesDhuhrRaw": "Put Dhuhr on the calendar before the workday takes over.||Stand without carrying the whole task list into salah.||If you pray Sunnah prayers, place them around the fard according to your learned practice.",
  "prayerBestPracticesAsrRaw": "Guard Asr from being pushed to the edge of the time.||Lower the pace before takbir so the prayer does not feel like a race.||Use Asr as an accountability checkpoint for the rest of the day.",
  "prayerBestPracticesMaghribRaw": "Respond quickly when Maghrib enters.||Keep sunset meals and gatherings from delaying the prayer.||Let Maghrib open your evening adhkar and family calm.",
  "prayerBestPracticesIshaRaw": "Pray before exhaustion dulls attention.||Keep Witr visible in the night routine according to your practice.||Prepare the body and room for Fajr before sleeping.",
  "learnQuranTextMapRaw": ""
}
